{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nCompletion-verification is single-pass and, by contract, emits findings ONLY for FAILING\ncriteria (`reconcile_verdict` flips a PASS-with-findings to FAIL). On a PASS it persists just\nsigned counts via the attestation â€” no per-criterion record exists anywhere, and the FAIL-only\nsidecar never fires. So a successfully-closed ticket has no durable per-criterion completion\naudit, unlike its plan and code reviews.\n\n## What\n\n1. Extend the verifier's output contract with a positive per-criterion `criteria[]` array â€” one\n   `{criterion, met, citation, kind}` entry per acceptance/success criterion evaluated (met\n   status, a source-code or attestation citation, and its codebase-verifiable / operator-attested\n   kind). This rides ALONGSIDE the failures-only `findings`; a PASS keeps `findings == []`.\n2. Emit a completion sidecar on PASS (not only FAIL) persisting that array plus the verdict,\n   runner, model, and material fingerprint.\n\nCompletion stays single-pass â€” this adds a per-criterion result list, NOT a four-pass structure.\n\n## Schema-version strategy (explicit)\n\nDo NOT bump the existing FAIL schema. Keep `SCHEMA_FAIL = \"completion_verifier_fail_v1\"`\nunchanged (so `latest_fail_verdict` and the existing FAIL-record tests are untouched). Add a\nSECOND constant `SCHEMA_PASS = \"completion_verifier_pass_v1\"` for PASS records; `build_payload`\npicks the schema by verdict. This keeps `test_fail_close_persists_durable_verdict` and\n`test_pass_close_leaves_no_fail_record` green (a PASS record is a different schema, so\n`latest_fail_verdict` still returns None on a PASS).\n\nThe `kind` field vocabulary is the CLOSED set `{\"codebase-verifiable\", \"operator-attested\"}`\n(matching ADR 0043's two criterion kinds); `met` is a bool; `citation` reuses the shared\n`Citation` shape (nullable).\n\n## Scope (enumerated edit targets)\n\n- `src/rebar/llm/contracts.py` â€” **load-bearing**: `CompletionVerdict` is a pydantic `BaseModel`\n  with no `extra=\"allow\"`, so pydantic v2 DROPS any `criteria[]` the agent emits unless it is a\n  declared field. Add a `Criterion` sub-model (`{criterion: str, met: bool, citation: Citation |\n  None, kind: str}`) and a `criteria: list[Criterion] = Field(default_factory=list)` field to\n  `CompletionVerdict`.\n- `src/rebar/schemas/completion_verdict.schema.json` â€” add the OPTIONAL `criteria[]` property\n  (items `{criterion, met, citation, kind}`); `findings` stays required, `criteria` optional. The\n  modelâ†”schema PARITY test\n  (`tests/interfaces/store/test_completion_verifier.py::test_completion_verdict_pins_to_schema`)\n  asserts the model's field set equals the schema's property set, so it MUST be UPDATED in lockstep\n  to include `criteria` (it will NOT pass unchanged) â€” this is an expected, in-scope test edit.\n- `src/rebar/schemas/completion_reconcile_input.schema.json` â€” **required because this schema is\n  `additionalProperties: false`**: add a `raw_criteria` (array) property, else the workflow's\n  `completion_reconcile` step would reject/not-carry the criteria. (The verify step's `criteria`\n  output must be threaded into the reconcile step â€” see the YAML edit below.)\n- `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gates/completion-verification.yaml` â€” in the `completion_reconcile`\n  step's `with:`, thread `raw_criteria: ${{ steps.verify.outputs.criteria }}` (alongside the\n  existing `raw_verdict`/`raw_findings`), so the agent's positive array reaches the reconcile op.\n- `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_ops.py` â€” `completion_reconcile(ctx)` reads `raw_criteria` from\n  `ctx.inputs` and sets `result[\"criteria\"] = list(ctx.inputs.get(\"raw_criteria\") or [])` on the\n  reconciled verdict BEFORE `validate_structured`, so the workflow (close-gate) path carries\n  `criteria[]` end-to-end â€” not only the bespoke `verify_completion` path.\n- `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/completion_verifier.md` â€” update the prompt: instruct the agent to\n  emit `criteria[]` with one met-record per evaluated criterion (each with citation + kind).\n  `findings` stays failures-only.\n- `src/rebar/llm/completion.py` â€” `reconcile_verdict` must NOT flip a PASS that carries a\n  populated `criteria[]` but empty `findings` (it keys the flip on `findings`; ensure `criteria[]`\n  is not stripped and add the regression test).\n- `src/rebar/llm/completion_sidecar.py` â€” the existing constant is named `SCHEMA` (value\n  `\"completion_verifier_fail_v1\"`). Do NOT rename it (that would churn the FAIL reader + its\n  tests); keep `SCHEMA` as the FAIL schema and ADD a second constant\n  `SCHEMA_PASS = \"completion_verifier_pass_v1\"`. `build_payload` branches on the verdict\n  (PASS â†’ `SCHEMA_PASS` + `criteria[]`; FAIL â†’ unchanged `SCHEMA` + `findings`); add\n  `latest_pass_record(ticket_id)` mirroring `latest_fail_verdict` but schema-guarded to\n  `SCHEMA_PASS`. `latest_fail_verdict` (guarded to `SCHEMA`) is untouched, so a PASS record is\n  invisible to it and the existing FAIL tests stay green.\n- `src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py` â€” on the PASS path (after the verdict is confirmed\n  PASS, before `_verdict_manifest` signs), add a best-effort `completion_sidecar.emit(result,\n  material=â€¦, repo_root=repo_root)` (swallow its own errors â€” persistence is observability, never\n  load-bearing on the close). Set `result.setdefault(\"ticket_id\", resolved_id)` first.\n\n## Compatibility & rollback\n\n`criteria[]` is OPTIONAL â€” an older agent/response that omits it yields today's behavior (PASS\ncounts only), and the failures-only `findings` invariant is unchanged, so nothing regresses. No\nbackfill. Reverting stops the PASS-path emit and drops the field; existing FAIL records stay\nreadable (their schema is untouched).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A completion PASS returns a `criteria[]` array with one met-record per evaluated criterion\n      and `findings` stays empty. Oracle: a unit test on `reconcile_verdict` feeding a PASS\n      verdict with a populated `criteria[]`, asserting it is NOT flipped to FAIL and the array\n      survives; plus a test that the `CompletionVerdict` pydantic model round-trips `criteria[]`\n      (proving it is not dropped).\n- [ ] A completion PASS emits a `completion_verifier_pass_v1` sidecar persisting the per-criterion\n      array. Oracle: an integration test that closes a ticket through the gate with a stub verifier\n      returning the new PASS shape and asserts on the emitted event JSON (via the real sidecar\n      emit path), plus that `latest_pass_record` reads it back.\n- [ ] Live end-to-end: running the real completion verifier (`[agents]` extra + API key) on a\n      fixture ticket whose criteria are met produces a PASS with a populated `criteria[]`\n      persisted to the sidecar. Oracle: a live/E2E test exercising the real agent path, gated on\n      LLM availability (skipped with a recorded reason otherwise).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784074353882658001,"uuid":"644eec01-22bf-436b-9a39-8842145b735b"}